### Tic Tac Toe API — REST Client Tests
### Install "REST Client" extension in VS Code, then click "Send Request"

@base = http://localhost:3000/api

### ── Players ────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Create a player
POST {{base}}/players
Content-Type: application/json

{ "username": "alice", "displayName": "Alice" }

###

# Get player profile
GET {{base}}/players/alice

###

# Leaderboard
GET {{base}}/leaderboard?limit=5

###

### ── Games ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Start PvC (vs AI, Hard)
POST {{base}}/games
Content-Type: application/json

{ "mode": "PvC", "difficulty": "hard", "playerX": "alice" }

###

# Start PvP
POST {{base}}/games
Content-Type: application/json

{ "mode": "PvP", "playerX": "alice", "playerO": "bob" }

###

# Get game state (replace 1 with your game ID)
GET {{base}}/games/1

###

# Make a move — position 4 (center), player alice
POST {{base}}/games/1/move
Content-Type: application/json

{ "position": 4, "player": "alice" }

###

# Get move history
GET {{base}}/games/1/moves

###

# List all active games
GET {{base}}/games?status=active

###

# Abandon a game
DELETE {{base}}/games/1

###
